<h2 id="section-top">Skin cancer services</h2>
</div>
<div class="col four-sm">
</div>
<div class="col three-sm" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn1">
<div class="box">
<p class="module">
        This Department is managed by  
        <a href="/Services/Trusts/Overview/DefaultView.aspx?id=2012">Imperial College Healthcare NHS Trust</a>
</p>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div id="imageContent0838f331b7b7481a9b3e30985709b3d0">
</div>
<p>Our <a href="https://www.imperial.nhs.uk/our-services/cancer-services/skin-cancer">skin cancer services</a> examines and diagnoses patients with suspected skin cancers.</p>
<p>At these clinics we perform tests to rule out or diagnose skin cancer. If treatment is required it will be started as early as possible. Skin we treat are cancers:</p>
<ul>
<li>actinic keratosis (also known as solar keratosis)</li>
<li>basal cell carcinoma (rodent ulcer)</li>
<li>squamous cell carcinoma</li>
<li>melanoma</li>
</ul>
<p>If treatment is required this will usually be decided on the day of the appointment to avoid delay.</p></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="col two-sm last" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn2">
<div class="panel panel-treatments-offered" id="listContainer59902ed3ff134015bb58587c70bc19ba">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div class="module">
<h3>Treatments and services offered at the Skin cancer services department </h3>
</div>
<ul>
<li>Actinic keratosis (also known as solar keratosis)</li>
<li>Basal cell carcinoma (rodent ulcer)</li>
<li>Melanoma</li>
<li>Squamous cell carcinoma</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
